data.name: label61.Text
data.value:
Wheels width influences coupling with road. Wheels position influences handling and stability at driving. Try to avoid too wide and a narrow position.
Wheels diameter is logical(not visible) and physical(visible). We can't see logical values, but game will operate car as you set in the logical values. Visible values we can see, but game would ignore this settings. So if u want normal settings, set logical values equals physical values.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value: It is possible to "take" handling from any other car from game, for this purpose choose it from the list and press to "Apply"

data.name: label51.Text
data.value: The car drive defines a leading axis at the current car, at a full upgrade (3 level). For example, if it is the drag-car it is necessary to put a back drive(RWD), for drift, back(RWD) or full(4WD). Though in Underground2 drift on a forward drive(FWD) goes well, though in a real life it is silly and it is almost unreal.

data.name: label9.Text
data.value: The car suspension bracket very strongly influences on handling. Too high suspension bracket will disturb on turns, but any noob player can do wheelie :D Do not put too low suspension bracket, differently the car will disappear!

data.name: label16.Text
data.value: In the next versions of the program to regulate values it will not be necessary manually. There will be a simple adjustment with help TrackBars and/or pictures, like in game. If you have any ideas for this program, write to us, our contacts and e-mail you will find in the "Help" section.
